<br>
Nice way to sneak changes in &quot;again.&quot; <br>
<br>
****************<br>
<br>
I was the one that proposed this to the other mods.  I closely follwed the discussions here, on the rants board, how many were being reserved and the poll.  In my opinion hanging onto a reservation on a mob that was not being utilized was making us look like we didn't care that the server was a changing entity that was out-growing certain areas of the reservation system.  As such I posted that in the moderators forum and asked that we take a step in removing them.<br>
<br>
The reservations system works because people respect them, and they respect the rights of others to use them.  If people think that they are not vaild because they are being under-utilized then a change should be made.   We should not make the reservation system stagnate because we refused to acknowledge that the server is changing.<br>
<br>
Now, before you direct anymore attacks at Jaradis, find fault in my reasons and choose to disagree with them, not a moderator.  I was the one that spearheaded the change, the other moderators agreed.  It was not a decision made by any one person on this board. <p><center><img src=http://www.castlerigby.com/images/kestrisig2.jpg>
